The paper discusses a prototype web-based question answering system and the use of probabilistic models and cost-benefit analyses to guide resource-intensive procedures. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Computer Science that deal with natural language processing (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and databases (cs.DB).
